    Unit 1

              

    Getting Started 

    Lambda Leadership provides an opportunity for you to build your skills as a team member and leader while here at Lambda, and prepares you for your work on a team in the industry. As part of the program, you'll participate in both Track Teams and Peer Mentorship.

    In Slack, you'll be introduced to your Track Team channel and to your mentor. Keep an eye on your Slack notifications, as well as messages from Slackbot.

    You'll also have a dedicated Student Leadership staff member who can help you navigate your Lambda Leadership experience, answer questions, as well as provide support and coaching on leadership, mentorship, and team skills. To find your assigned Student Leadership staff member, check your Track Team channel.

    Peer Mentorship - What to Expect

    With peer mentorship, you'll work with others to build your technical vocabulary and team skills.

    By learning to talk about your code and break down complex information to your fellow peers (and future colleagues!), you're helping to solidify your technical knowledge and building the skills you'll need to navigate interviews and the workplace.

    Take a look at the link below to learn more:

    Peer Mentorship: Overview & Conversation Guides  

    Track Teams

      

    Your Track Team is a place for you to build your community at Lambda and an opportunity for you to grow your network. It's a great way to get different perspectives on a project you might be working on and develop your collaboration skills, as well as a place to reach out to with questions when you're feeling stuck and need some help debugging!

    With your team, you'll also participate in team skill-building exercises to further strengthen and develop your skills in communication, conflict management, and project management, all of which will help set you up for success in Build Weeks, Labs, and on the job.

    Remember, your team experience is shaped by you - so during your time at Lambda, make the most of this opportunity and help build the team and community you want to be a part of.

    Learn more: Track Teams: Unit 1
